headline: Oracle's 'truly awesome' quarter stuns Wall Street, sending stock up 36% and making Ellison world's richest man
summary: Oracle's massive backlog for its cloud business stunned Wall Street Wednesday, cementing its spot as a key player in the AI market and lifting hopes that the AI-fueled tech rally has more room to run.

headline: This week in banking: Top execs sound upbeat on quarter, less certain on economy
summary: Some of the nation's top bankers struck upbeat tones on the US consumer and their own earnings this week while voicing uncertainty about the road ahead for the US economy.

headline: ‘Key AI enabler’: BofA upgrades Oracle to Buy after exceptional Q1 print
summary: Investing.com -- Bank of America (BofA) upgraded Oracle to Buy from Neutral, raising its price objective to $368 from $295, after the software company delivered an impressive first-quarter showing that reinforced its growing role in artificial intelligence infrastructure.
